So I was waiting for my clients in Houston to show up for their shoot, while waiting, I saw this beautiful young lady come out with her 2 sisters and they were taking pictures of her. So while waiting I came out and asked, is it her prom? And they said no, she’s celebrating Quinceañera. I was like awwww, would you like me to take some professional pictures for you? They said sure why not! So I took the shot and showed her and the tears that came from her eyes reminded me of why I love doing my job! They asked me how much do they have to pay me and I told them, it’s on me. Thank you for the reminder. Sometimes this becomes just another job, so it’s good to remember why we take up that camera. 🥰
